    "Additionally, it randomly resizes input images during the training phase to improve the network's capacity to detect objects at different scales.",
    "In contrast to YOLOv1, which relies solely on down-sampling to bolster the high-resolution classifier for small object detection, YOLOv2 utilizes multiple layers to transmit high-resolution features to the detector.",
    "With the release of YOLOv3 (Redmon and Farhadi, 2018), real-time object identification has significantly advanced, showcasing impressive improvements in both speed and accuracy.",
    "To improve feature extraction performance and mitigate deterioration in deeper neural networks, a robust Darknet-53 architecture is implemented, consisting of 53 convolutional layers with residual connections.",
    "The multi-class probabilistic classifier, featuring independent classes and pyramidal forecasts, integrated into YOLOv3's innovative design, revolutionizes object recognition precision."
